1
00:00:04,863 --> 00:00:07,103
The general strategy is

2
00:00:07,103 --> 00:00:12,186
to invite the Lord’s mercy

3
00:00:12,586 --> 00:00:17,361
towards someone who would be

4
00:00:17,500 --> 00:00:25,880
a very good example
for redemption.

5
00:00:26,142 --> 00:00:29,116
[“Redeem Me!”]

6
00:00:29,576 --> 00:00:31,819
So sometimes the devotees are saying,

7
00:00:31,819 --> 00:00:34,343
“If You want to test Your mercy

8
00:00:34,343 --> 00:00:36,281
and its purifying capacity,

9
00:00:36,711 --> 00:00:41,303
there’s no better specimen

10
00:00:41,593 --> 00:00:44,788
than myself, as a fallen soul.”

11
00:00:50,724 --> 00:00:53,462
And it is a genuine feeling.

12
00:00:55,200 --> 00:00:57,912
I said to Śrīla Guru Mahārāj once that,

13
00:00:58,146 --> 00:00:59,956
“If Kaviraj Goswami …”

14
00:00:59,956 --> 00:01:04,332
He says, you know, 
“Jagāi mādhāi haite muñi se pāpiṣṭha

15
00:01:04,332 --> 00:01:07,378
purīṣera kīṭa haite muñi se laghiṣṭha:

16
00:01:07,378 --> 00:01:11,728
‘I’m more sinful than Jagāi and Mādhāi.

17
00:01:11,820 --> 00:01:19,234
If you hear my name,
you’ll lose your pious credits.

18
00:01:19,302 --> 00:01:22,204
If you chant my name,
you’ll fall down.

19
00:01:22,256 --> 00:01:24,663
I’m lower than the worm
in a stool’ [Cc: 1.5.205].”

20
00:01:24,663 --> 00:01:25,981
Saying so many …

21
00:01:25,981 --> 00:01:28,220
venting so much negativity.

22
00:01:28,220 --> 00:01:30,074
So I said to Guru Mahārāj,

23
00:01:30,074 --> 00:01:33,461
“It’s one thing that Kavirāj Goswāmī
is saying this,”

24
00:01:33,461 --> 00:01:36,695
I said,
“but what if you actually are

25
00:01:36,818 --> 00:01:40,892
more sinful 
than Jagāi and Mādhāi?”

26
00:01:41,753 --> 00:01:44,287
And Guru Mahārāj said “Oh!

27
00:01:44,287 --> 00:01:49,667
Then perhaps this plenary power
is descending in you.”

28
00:01:49,940 --> 00:01:51,968
Meaning:

29
00:01:51,968 --> 00:01:59,700
Kavirāj Goswāmī doesn’t think he’s speaking
cleverly, poetically, euphemistically;

30
00:01:59,700 --> 00:02:02,941
it’s a sincere expression 
from his heart,

31
00:02:02,941 --> 00:02:08,481
on account of the depth of his positive
penetration into Kṛṣṇa conception

32
00:02:08,497 --> 00:02:11,575
—‘dive deep into Reality’—

33
00:02:11,589 --> 00:02:16,023
that he can vent such negativity.

34
00:02:16,368 --> 00:02:22,133
So it’s not a posing; it’s a sincere,
heartfelt expression.

